parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The coolant leak can cause steam to come through the vents, reducing visibility while driving, and potentially leading to accidents. Additionally, the leak can cause damage to the vehicle's electrical systems and interior components.

steam coming through the vents

coolant splashing all over the vehicle.

radiator and heater core failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The front oil seal failure can cause oil leaks, leading to engine damage, overheating, and potentially causing accidents.

front oil seal failure
fuses failing at the fuel pump.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Automatic Seat Belt Upper Torso Buckle Malfunction
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning automatic seat belt upper torso buckle can cause the buckle to stick out, potentially striking the driver's or passenger's head, leading to injury or distraction while driving.
symptoms: The automatic seat belt upper torso buckle sticks out

the buckle fails to retract properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The automatic seat belt locking issue can cause the seat belts to become stuck, making it difficult or impossible to use them properly, which can increase the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The driver's and passenger's side automatic seat belts lock into the unit and will not come out
the seat belts fail to retract properly
the seat belts are stuck in the retracted position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The manual seat belt failure can cause the seat belts to become loose or fail to lock in place, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.

the seat belts do not lock in place when the brakes are applied
the seat belts fail to provide adequate restraint.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The retractor and lap belt failure can cause the seat belts to become stuck or fail to release, making it difficult or impossible to use them properly, which can increase the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The passenger and driver shoulder belts stick with poor retractors
the lap belts fail to release
the seat belts are difficult to use.
